'''Assumption Island day Gecko''' ('''''Phelsuma abbotti sumptio''''' <small>[[Anthony S. Cheke|Cheke]], 1982</small>), named after a small island outlying on the south west end of the [[Seychelles]] is a [[subspecies]] of [[gecko]]s. This gecko is only found on [[Assumption Island]]. It typically reaches the length of 140&nbsp;mm, lives on palm trees and feeds on [[insect]]s and fruit.

{{Taxonbar|from=Q4810364}}

